1
00:00:08,867 --> 00:00:11,004
OK. Time to go.

2
00:00:11,004 --> 00:00:12,373
Sis.

3
00:00:14,641 --> 00:00:18,345
[door opens, shuts]

4
00:00:18,345 --> 00:00:20,914
[theme song plays]

5
00:00:25,119 --> 00:00:27,421
[woman singing in Japanese]

6
00:01:51,037 --> 00:01:53,073
[girl] Good morning.

7
00:01:56,910 --> 00:02:00,147
Ah! I'm so glad you're finally
back, Otosaka!

8
00:02:00,147 --> 00:02:01,982
[Takajo] It's good to see you.

9
00:02:01,982 --> 00:02:05,319
Thanks. Sorry it's been
so crazy. Uggh!

10
00:02:05,319 --> 00:02:07,188
[various students] Just because
he's a little handsome...

11
00:02:07,188 --> 00:02:09,022
Screw that jerk...
Can't believe this!

12
00:02:09,022 --> 00:02:12,092
Hey, we get it.
There's really no need
for you to apologize.

13
00:02:12,092 --> 00:02:17,298
Absolutely. We're just glad
to have the student council
back together again.

14
00:02:18,632 --> 00:02:20,901
<i>That's why I've decided</i>
<i>to stick with you</i>

15
00:02:20,901 --> 00:02:24,205
<i>until this is through</i>
<i>and you're back to normal.</i>

16
00:02:24,205 --> 00:02:26,573
[Yusa] I have a gift
for you, Otosaka.

17
00:02:26,573 --> 00:02:29,476
A magic spell
to celebrate your return.

18
00:02:29,476 --> 00:02:31,445
What? It can't be!

19
00:02:31,445 --> 00:02:32,679
[cheery music plays]

20
00:02:32,679 --> 00:02:34,915
Now, everything is wonderful.

21
00:02:34,915 --> 00:02:36,517
You just needed some time.

22
00:02:36,517 --> 00:02:40,621
Now the past is in the past
and you're gonna be fine!

23
00:02:40,621 --> 00:02:42,123
There it is!

24
00:02:42,123 --> 00:02:46,793
The memorable Yusarin
Magic Spell series, number one!

25
00:02:46,793 --> 00:02:49,796
It's the magic spell of...
you're gonna be fine!

26
00:02:49,796 --> 00:02:53,033
The very first day of her show,
this infamous magic spell idea

27
00:02:53,033 --> 00:02:55,436
dominated
the fortune‐telling segment!

28
00:02:55,436 --> 00:02:56,803
Enough!

29
00:02:56,803 --> 00:02:58,572
Hey, good morning, Yusarin.

30
00:02:58,572 --> 00:03:01,275
I just reserved your new single.
I'm so excited!

31
00:03:01,275 --> 00:03:03,844
‐I bought five copies.
‐I got six.

32
00:03:05,412 --> 00:03:07,748
‐[Takajo] You poseurs.
‐[others gasp]

33
00:03:07,748 --> 00:03:10,851
[Yu thinking] <i>I'm actually</i>
<i>thankful for their annoying</i>
<i>cheerfulness.</i>

34
00:03:10,851 --> 00:03:12,253
<i>Who'd have thought?</i>

35
00:03:12,253 --> 00:03:14,755
<i>Makes me feel like</i>
<i>I can be myself again.</i>

36
00:03:14,755 --> 00:03:19,626
<i>Come to think of it, I should</i>
<i>apologize to Shirayanagi</i>
<i>next time.</i>

37
00:03:19,626 --> 00:03:21,762
<i>I was pretty awful to her.</i>

38
00:03:21,762 --> 00:03:23,630
About the new single...

39
00:03:23,630 --> 00:03:25,632
Ta‐da! It's the music video

40
00:03:25,632 --> 00:03:28,635
that comes with the first press
of my brand‐new single!

41
00:03:28,635 --> 00:03:31,205
‐[all] I wanna see it!
‐[Tomori] Knock it off!

42
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:35,008
[Takajo] Meet you
in the cafeteria?

43
00:03:35,008 --> 00:03:36,643
‐Yeah.
‐[whoosh!]

44
00:03:36,643 --> 00:03:40,914
‐[Takajo groans]
‐[Yu] Here we go.
‐[bell ringing]

45
00:03:40,914 --> 00:03:45,419
Here it is, nice and hot.
Enjoy.

46
00:03:45,419 --> 00:03:49,290
You know, you didn't
have to go through this
just to welcome me back.

47
00:03:49,290 --> 00:03:51,225
[Takajo] Don't read
too much into it.

48
00:03:51,225 --> 00:03:52,759
I just had a craving for it.

49
00:03:52,759 --> 00:03:55,229
I haven't had this limited menu
for a while myself.

50
00:03:55,229 --> 00:03:57,398
[Yu] <i>I can read him</i>
<i>like an open book.</i>

51
00:03:57,398 --> 00:04:01,101
<i>But I shall appreciate and</i>
<i>accept his kindness for now.</i>

52
00:04:01,101 --> 00:04:04,105
I'm really glad
that I can have this again.

53
00:04:04,105 --> 00:04:05,606
Thanks a lot.

54
00:04:05,606 --> 00:04:07,241
[both] Time to dig in.

55
00:04:09,610 --> 00:04:11,044
I forgot how good it was.

56
00:04:11,044 --> 00:04:14,615
Right? No matter how many times
I eat this, it never gets old.

57
00:04:14,615 --> 00:04:16,383
[phone vibrates]

58
00:04:16,383 --> 00:04:19,052
We gotta go.
We'll have to scarf it down.

59
00:04:19,052 --> 00:04:22,389
That guy is gonna show up again,
isn't he?

60
00:04:24,225 --> 00:04:27,194
Jeez, you're slow.
What is your zodiac sign again?

61
00:04:27,194 --> 00:04:30,397
[Yu] You always call
when we're eating!

62
00:04:30,397 --> 00:04:32,733
[Tomori] Well, now that
everyone is here,

63
00:04:32,733 --> 00:04:34,968
I guess we'll start by watching
Kurobane's music video.

64
00:04:34,968 --> 00:04:37,838
‐[Yu] Huh?
‐I don't know,
I'm so embarrassed!

65
00:04:37,838 --> 00:04:40,574
Ohh! All right!

66
00:04:40,574 --> 00:04:43,043
I'll get to see it
before anyone else does!

67
00:04:43,043 --> 00:04:44,778
Ha ha ha! Waaah!

68
00:04:44,778 --> 00:04:46,280
Don't worry, Yusa.

69
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:48,182
Even if the video sucks
out loud,

70
00:04:48,182 --> 00:04:51,518
someone here will still love it.

71
00:04:51,518 --> 00:04:54,121
♪

