<i>♪ Nani mo wakaranai ♪</i>

92
00:06:31,818 --> 00:06:35,122
<i>♪ I can do it too</i>
<i>once I'm there with you ♪</i>

93
00:06:38,459 --> 00:06:41,595
[Yusa] Thanks for listening.
I really hoped you enjoyed it.

94
00:06:41,595 --> 00:06:44,998
[Yu] Well, give her
some kind of feedback.

95
00:06:44,998 --> 00:06:47,901
Haaaa...

96
00:06:47,901 --> 00:06:49,403
Hey.

97
00:06:49,403 --> 00:06:52,606
‐Huh. It's pretty good, I guess.
‐Huh?

98
00:06:52,606 --> 00:06:55,809
Yusarin's so happy.
She got a compliment from you!

99
00:06:55,809 --> 00:06:59,280
Well, now I'm docking points
since you spoke
in the third person.

100
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:00,981
[both gasp]

101
00:07:00,981 --> 00:07:05,186
Out of curiosity, Tomori, around
how many points do I have total?

102
00:07:05,186 --> 00:07:08,189
Ten for singing,
20 for the song,

103
00:07:08,189 --> 00:07:11,192
20 for the costume,
30 for the editing,

104
00:07:11,192 --> 00:07:13,560
and minus‐51 for the singer
being pathetic.

105
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:16,197
‐OK...
‐So that means she has...

106
00:07:16,197 --> 00:07:17,598
A total of 29 points.

107
00:07:17,598 --> 00:07:19,533
Huh? You just flunked Yusa!

108
00:07:19,533 --> 00:07:23,370
But what would it be
if you scored it based
on the music video alone?

109
00:07:23,370 --> 00:07:25,106
Around 80 points.

110
00:07:25,106 --> 00:07:27,040
‐Yay!
‐That's much better.

111
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:29,543
All right,
Yusarin's so happy!

112
00:07:29,543 --> 00:07:31,245
It just dropped down
to 19 points.

113
00:07:31,245 --> 00:07:32,713
[screams]

114
00:07:32,713 --> 00:07:35,582
But that score makes Yusa sound
like a total idiot.

115
00:07:35,582 --> 00:07:39,120
Well, I suppose I could judge it
from a business standpoint.

116
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:41,455
In which case,
it's a perfect 100.

117
00:07:41,455 --> 00:07:44,057
Really? That's pretty unusual
for you.

118
00:07:44,057 --> 00:07:47,461
‐All right, I'm so happy!
‐Wow, you did it, Yusarin.

119
00:07:47,461 --> 00:07:49,630
I wanna watch it again!

120
00:07:49,630 --> 00:07:52,233
[Tomori] Fine.
But it's the last time.

121
00:07:52,233 --> 00:07:56,303
<i>♪ I can do it too</i>
<i>once I'm there with you ♪</i>

122
00:07:58,705 --> 00:08:01,375
[Yu] Jeez, what's taking
this guy so long?

123
00:08:01,375 --> 00:08:03,144
Oh, he's not coming today.

124
00:08:03,144 --> 00:08:05,512
[Yu] Huh? Then what did
you call us for?

125
00:08:05,512 --> 00:08:08,582
Calm down.
It'll be worth it.

126
00:08:08,582 --> 00:08:10,117
Voilà!

127
00:08:10,117 --> 00:08:11,852
Uh‐huh. Let's see.

128
00:08:11,852 --> 00:08:14,421
Looks like these are tickets
to a Zhiend concert.

129
00:08:14,421 --> 00:08:16,123
And they're for
tomorrow night's performance.

130
00:08:16,123 --> 00:08:17,891
What's "The End"?

131
00:08:17,891 --> 00:08:20,261
I thought you would have
heard of them, Yusa.

132
00:08:20,261 --> 00:08:23,264
Zhiend is the rock band
Tomori likes so much.

133
00:08:23,264 --> 00:08:25,532
It's post‐rock.
Get it right, moron!

134
00:08:25,532 --> 00:08:27,301
[Takajo] Uh, post‐rock?

135
00:08:27,301 --> 00:08:28,869
Look it up on Wiki.

136
00:08:28,869 --> 00:08:30,971
[Takajo] Now I'm even more
confused.

137
00:08:30,971 --> 00:08:33,407
You don't have to understand it
to see them.

138
00:08:33,407 --> 00:08:36,743
Look, I have two tickets to see
the greatest band ever.

139
00:08:36,743 --> 00:08:39,346
You're here to help me figure
out what to do with them.

140
00:08:39,346 --> 00:08:42,716
Wait, I don't get it.
What else do you do
with tickets?

141
00:08:42,716 --> 00:08:45,452
I think she needs one of us
to take the second one.

142
00:08:45,452 --> 00:08:47,087
Otherwise it's a waste.

143
00:08:47,087 --> 00:08:48,455
Oh, I see.

144
00:08:48,455 --> 00:08:50,357
But I don't know about
that something‐rock.

145
00:08:50,357 --> 00:08:52,058
It sounds kind of bizarre.

146
00:08:52,058 --> 00:08:56,630
[groans] Their reviews
and popularity overseas
are super high.

147
00:08:56,630 --> 00:08:59,633
If your song was a perfect score
at 100 points,

148
00:08:59,633 --> 00:09:01,435
Zhiend would score
a million easy.

149
00:09:01,435 --> 00:09:04,271
Wait! You're saying their score
is higher than perfect?!

150
00:09:04,271 --> 00:09:07,974
[Tomori] So, do I have
any volunteers?

151
00:09:07,974 --> 00:09:11,512
Hmm... I don't have much
of an interest, honestly.

152
00:09:11,512 --> 00:09:13,514
Guess you're taking
one for the team, Otosaka.

153
00:09:13,514 --> 00:09:15,882
‐Huh? Why me?
‐That's perfect.

154
00:09:15,882 --> 00:09:18,819
‐I think the two of you
will have a great time.
‐Wait!

155
00:09:18,819 --> 00:09:20,854
You can't just decide by
process of elimination.

156
00:09:20,854 --> 00:09:23,957
I know, why don't we ask Misa?
She'll probably dig it a lot.

157
00:09:23,957 --> 00:09:27,661
Only if I can listen
to a super‐fast two‐bass
at 260 BPM.

158
00:09:27,661 --> 00:09:32,366
You won't get a super‐fast
two‐bass at 260 BPM, so you
might as well forget it.

159
00:09:32,366 --> 00:09:34,168
Looks like
it's all decided, Otosaka.

160
00:09:34,168 --> 00:09:36,170
‐Enjoy the concert.
‐[Yu sighs]

161
00:09:36,170 --> 00:09:38,839
[Yu] <i>Can I afford</i>
<i>to indulge like this?</i>

162
00:09:38,839 --> 00:09:41,375
[Tomori] It's OK
every once in a while.

163
00:09:41,375 --> 00:09:43,844
People do need breathers.

164
00:09:46,580 --> 00:09:49,283
[Yu] All right, guess I'm going.

165
00:09:56,523 --> 00:09:58,425
Uh, excuse me.

166
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,862
[Yu] <i>A foreigner?</i>

167
00:10:03,764 --> 00:10:07,301
[woman, softly]
Why avoid me? Jeez!

168
00:10:09,470 --> 00:10:10,737
[Yu gasps]

169
00:10:10,737 --> 00:10:14,007
[Yu] <i>What... was that?</i>

170
00:10:14,007 --> 00:10:16,310
<i>It can't be.</i>

171
00:10:16,310 --> 00:10:19,780
Hey, wait. Do you...
understand me?

172
00:10:19,780 --> 00:10:24,385
[woman] Take me somewhere
I can eat modern yaki, pronto.

173
00:10:24,385 --> 00:10:26,587
[Yu] Uh, I'm sorry,
what did you say?

174
00:10:26,587 --> 00:10:30,957
You got sand in your ears?
Mo‐dern ya‐ki, now.

175
00:10:30,957 --> 00:10:33,594
‐Modern yaki?
‐You gotta be kidding.

176
00:10:33,594 --> 00:10:37,298
Nobody seems to know.
What the hell is with Japan
these days?

177
00:10:37,298 --> 00:10:39,133
Jesus!

178
00:10:39,133 --> 00:10:42,136
[Yu] Are you talking
about okonomiyaki
with noodles in it?

179
00:10:42,136 --> 00:10:45,506
Yes, noodles!
That's exactly what I want.
Is there a place nearby?

180
00:10:45,506 --> 00:10:47,774
[Yu] If you don't mind it
being Hiroshima yaki,

181
00:10:47,774 --> 00:10:49,710
you can find it
in any hole‐in‐the‐wall.

182
00:10:49,710 --> 00:10:52,078
‐[woman] Does it have
noodles in it?
‐Uh, yeah.

183
00:10:52,078 --> 00:10:55,416
‐[woman] Then let's get going!
‐All right, all right,
I'll take you there.

184
00:10:55,416 --> 00:10:57,017
[waiter] Welcome.

185
00:10:57,017 --> 00:11:00,221
‐One Hiroshima yaki.
‐And a medium draft beer.

186
00:11:00,221 --> 00:11:01,922
Got it.

187
00:11:01,922 --> 00:11:05,292
‐Not for me.
I'll have oolong tea.
‐[waiter] Rock on.

188
00:11:05,292 --> 00:11:08,262
Oh, sorry, make that two
Hiroshima yakis.

189
00:11:08,262 --> 00:11:09,530
[waiter] No problem.

190
00:11:09,530 --> 00:11:11,765
<i>Even if I go home,</i>

191
00:11:11,765 --> 00:11:14,868
<i>nobody's gonna have dinner</i>
<i>ready for me anymore.</i>

192
00:11:16,503 --> 00:11:19,673
<i>I have to get used</i>
<i>to this lifestyle.</i>

193
00:11:26,247 --> 00:11:29,316
Aaaah!
Man, that hit the spot.

194
00:11:29,316 --> 00:11:31,152
You wanna cook it yourself?

195
00:11:31,152 --> 00:11:34,488
Oh, actually, she's blind
so would you mind
cooking it for us?

196
00:11:34,488 --> 00:11:38,425
Sure thing. Huh?
Hold on. This woman is blind?

197
00:11:38,425 --> 00:11:40,327
No way. Are you...?

198
00:11:40,327 --> 00:11:43,197
That's right,
the vocalist for Zhiend.

199
00:11:43,197 --> 00:11:45,266
I'm Sala Shane.

200
00:11:45,266 --> 00:11:46,833
[Yu] <i>I knew it.</i>

201
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:48,935
Wow! I can't believe Sala
dropped by

202
00:11:48,935 --> 00:11:51,372
my filthy
little okonomiyaki shop!

203
00:11:51,372 --> 00:11:53,607
I'm so excited
about the gig tomorrow.

204
00:11:53,607 --> 00:11:56,076
Please, can I get an autograph
on a signboard?

205
00:11:56,076 --> 00:11:58,512
[Sala] Sure. Love to.

206
00:11:58,512 --> 00:12:01,715
‐[Yu] I'm surprised she can
write that without seeing.
‐Here you go.

207
00:12:01,715 --> 00:12:04,017
You're the greatest!
And here's your food!

208
00:12:04,017 --> 00:12:05,986
Eat up and enjoy!

209
00:12:10,023 --> 00:12:11,225
Hmm.

210
00:12:11,225 --> 00:12:13,093
[Yu] Is there a problem?

211
00:12:13,093 --> 00:12:14,328
[Sala] Hmm...

212
00:12:14,328 --> 00:12:15,696
The pancake's thin.

213
00:12:15,696 --> 00:12:17,598
[Yu] I told you
it wasn't modern yaki.

214
00:12:17,598 --> 00:12:19,400
There are going to be
differences.

215
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:22,136
Oh, right.
But it's still good.

216
00:12:22,136 --> 00:12:24,505
Nothing less from Japan.

217
00:12:24,505 --> 00:12:28,775
[waiter] Thank you very much!
Can't wait to see you rock it!

218
00:12:28,775 --> 00:12:32,213
Sorry.
I was short on cash.

219
00:12:32,213 --> 00:12:33,947
[Sala] Eh, it's whatever.

220
00:12:33,947 --> 00:12:37,651
So, uh, did something bad
happen to you recently?

221
00:12:37,651 --> 00:12:41,355
‐Huh?
‐The way you breathe and talk
says a lot on its own.

222
00:12:41,355 --> 00:12:45,659
You've been oozing out despair
from the moment we first met.

223
00:12:45,659 --> 00:12:47,528
I don't talk about it.

224
00:12:47,528 --> 00:12:52,133
[Sala] If I had to guess,
I'd say you lost someone
very close to you.

225
00:12:52,133 --> 00:12:53,500
You're amazing.

226
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,068
That's exactly it.

227
00:12:55,068 --> 00:12:59,206
If you don't mind,
can you tell me about it?

228
00:13:07,848 --> 00:13:11,252
[Yu] Just the other day,
I lost my little sister.

229
00:13:11,252 --> 00:13:12,953
[Sala] Oh, my God!

230
00:13:12,953 --> 00:13:14,855
You've gone above and beyond
for me.

231
00:13:14,855 --> 00:13:18,959
The least I could do
is put up some smoke
for that sister of yours.

232
00:13:18,959 --> 00:13:21,228
Put up smoke?
You mean burn some incense?

233
00:13:21,228 --> 00:13:23,997
‐Yeah, incense.
‐No, you don't have
to go that far.

234
00:13:23,997 --> 00:13:26,533
[Sala] Come on,
I'm begging you here. Please?

235
00:13:26,533 --> 00:13:30,104
[Yu] All right, I get it.
Would you please quit bowing?

236
00:13:35,142 --> 00:13:38,245
[Yu] Hey, I have a favor
to ask you.

237
00:13:38,245 --> 00:13:39,513
[Sala] Hmm?

238
00:13:39,513 --> 00:13:42,015
There's someone
I'd like you to meet.

239
00:13:42,015 --> 00:13:45,819
They're siblings that really
love your band.

240
00:13:45,819 --> 00:13:48,689
Huh. It sounds like
those friends of yours

241
00:13:48,689 --> 00:13:50,757
aren't just ordinary fans.

242
00:13:50,757 --> 00:13:52,893
Uh, no, not really.

243
00:13:52,893 --> 00:13:55,762
Could you hold on just a second?

244
00:13:55,762 --> 00:13:57,764
[Yu] <i>I just realized</i>
<i>that this is</i>

245
00:13:57,764 --> 00:13:59,566
<i>the first time</i>
<i>I've ever called her.</i>

246
00:13:59,566 --> 00:14:01,468
<i>It feels weird.</i>

247
00:14:01,468 --> 00:14:04,171
[line ringing]

248
00:14:04,171 --> 00:14:07,073
‐[Tomori] Tomori here.
‐Hey, it's me, Otosaka.

249
00:14:07,073 --> 00:14:10,244
[Tomori] You're calling me?
That's weird.

250
00:14:10,244 --> 00:14:11,878
Is something wrong?

251
00:14:11,878 --> 00:14:14,881
OK, try not to freak out
too much when I tell you this,

252
00:14:14,881 --> 00:14:17,651
but the vocalist for Zhiend
is in my house as we speak!

253
00:14:17,651 --> 00:14:19,186
[Tomori] <i>And?</i>

254
00:14:19,186 --> 00:14:21,655
Huh? What's the deal?
You don't believe me?

255
00:14:21,655 --> 00:14:26,360
[Tomori] No, I believe you.
There's no reason
for you to lie.

256
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:29,163
<i>So, what do you want?</i>

257
00:14:29,163 --> 00:14:30,231
You can meet her.

258
00:14:30,231 --> 00:14:32,166
<i>What would be the point</i>
<i>of that?</i>

259
00:14:32,166 --> 00:14:35,369
[Yu] Oh, I don’t know.
You can talk to her, interact.

260
00:14:35,369 --> 00:14:38,805
<i>Sure, but I wouldn't go</i>
<i>out of my way to do that.</i>

261
00:14:38,805 --> 00:14:41,242
Look, I love Zhiend's music
and stage presence,

262
00:14:41,242 --> 00:14:45,312
so I just wanna listen to
their CDs and watch their gigs.
That's all.

263
00:14:45,312 --> 00:14:46,847
[Yu sighs]

264
00:14:46,847 --> 00:14:48,915
<i>Is that really</i>
<i>all you called me for?</i>

265
00:14:48,915 --> 00:14:51,285
‐I'm hanging up.
‐No, that's not it!

266
00:14:51,285 --> 00:14:55,088
<i>You're trying my patience here.</i>
<i>What is it?</i>

267
00:14:55,088 --> 00:14:59,760
Thanks for waiting.
The person I'd like you to meet
is still a little far from here.

268
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:01,962
When do you have to be back by?

269
00:15:01,962 --> 00:15:04,898
Time isn't really a factor, kid.
Don't worry.

270
00:15:04,898 --> 00:15:06,767
Take me wherever you'd like
to go.

271
00:15:06,767 --> 00:15:08,969
I know we only met
a few hours ago,

272
00:15:08,969 --> 00:15:12,939
but what's important to you
is already important to me
at this point.

273
00:15:12,939 --> 00:15:14,775
Are you sure that it's
all right?

274
00:15:14,775 --> 00:15:16,910
I mean, your gig
is happening tomorrow.

275
00:15:16,910 --> 00:15:19,513
[chuckles] The band members
and our producer

276
00:15:19,513 --> 00:15:21,215
will just have to make do
somehow.

277
00:15:21,215 --> 00:15:24,285
That helps a lot.
Thanks a bunch.

278
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:29,623
Oh, I have to tell her
I don't need dinner.

279
00:15:29,623 --> 00:15:32,759
Oh, damn it.
I did it again.

280
00:15:32,759 --> 00:15:35,362
She's not here anymore.
[sighs]

281
00:15:35,362 --> 00:15:39,133
And with that heavy sigh,
I've officially lost count.

282
00:15:39,133 --> 00:15:42,035
Did you remind yourself
of your little sister again?

283
00:15:43,970 --> 00:15:47,208
Wow, you see through pretty much
everything, don't you?

284
00:15:52,446 --> 00:15:54,281
Hey, I need food, stat.

285
00:15:54,281 --> 00:15:56,317
What? How is it possible
you're still hungry?

286
00:15:56,317 --> 00:15:59,820
That one was just lunch, silly.
Now it's time for dinner.

287
00:15:59,820 --> 00:16:02,022
OK, do you have something
in mind?

288
00:16:02,022 --> 00:16:06,026
After a relaxing train ride,
soba is the only choice.

289
00:16:07,561 --> 00:16:09,029
Great God in heaven!

290
00:16:09,029 --> 00:16:12,098
Croquet Soba is the most amazing
thing I've ever tasted!

291
00:16:14,501 --> 00:16:17,171
Ahh! What miraculous chemistry!

292
00:16:17,171 --> 00:16:20,474
I gotta pay my respects
to whoever came up with this.

293
00:16:20,474 --> 00:16:22,709
I'm so happy for you.

294
00:16:24,111 --> 00:16:26,513
[Yu] Hey, can I ask you
one thing?

295
00:16:26,513 --> 00:16:28,149
[Sala] Yeah, of course you can.

296
00:16:28,149 --> 00:16:30,284
Sorry if this is
a delicate question,

297
00:16:30,284 --> 00:16:33,520
but your eyes,
are they 100% blind?

298
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:35,722
Yep. I can't see a thing.

299
00:16:35,722 --> 00:16:37,791
But you can write autographs.

300
00:16:37,791 --> 00:16:40,861
I'm assuming that means you
weren't born blind, were you?

301
00:16:40,861 --> 00:16:43,530
No. But I've come to think of it
as my penance.

302
00:16:43,530 --> 00:16:44,865
Wait, penance?

303
00:16:44,865 --> 00:16:48,769
This is how I atone
for all my sins.

304
00:16:48,769 --> 00:16:52,173
Have you ever thought about
the great tragedy of life
before?

305
00:16:52,173 --> 00:16:54,074
That was
an abrupt change of topic.

306
00:16:54,074 --> 00:16:57,411
[Sala] Life is something
you only live once, right?

307
00:16:57,411 --> 00:16:59,079
[Yu] Of course.

308
00:16:59,079 --> 00:17:01,882
[Sala] I had dreamed
of spending my life
working on stage

309
00:17:01,882 --> 00:17:03,684
as the front man for a band.

310
00:17:03,684 --> 00:17:08,355
But my life was already
beyond hope before I knew it.

311
00:17:08,355 --> 00:17:11,292
And I couldn't grant myself
that dream.

312
00:17:11,292 --> 00:17:14,861
I was pitiful at both
singing and playing guitar

313
00:17:14,861 --> 00:17:19,300
and watched as people my age
were showered with praise
for their songs.

314
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:21,067
I hated God.

315
00:17:21,067 --> 00:17:23,570
OK, but aren't you living
that dream right now?

316
00:17:23,570 --> 00:17:27,073
‐Yes, but that's only because
I was able to cheat.
‐How so?

317
00:17:27,073 --> 00:17:31,077
[Sala] How isn't important.
The fact is that I was greedy.

318
00:17:31,077 --> 00:17:33,880
There was a time when I was
popular in Japan too.

319
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:39,186
A social phenomenon!
A person of the times.
That kind of success.

320
00:17:39,186 --> 00:17:41,588
When you're making
the kind of money I was,

321
00:17:41,588 --> 00:17:44,158
the people around you start
to look at you differently,

322
00:17:44,158 --> 00:17:45,659
and always for the worse.

323
00:17:45,659 --> 00:17:48,529
In the end, you even become
a threat to your family.

324
00:17:48,529 --> 00:17:51,798
My little brother was once
kidnapped for ransom.

325
00:17:51,798 --> 00:17:55,001
That's when I walked away
from the life.

326
00:17:55,001 --> 00:17:59,573
After that, I decided
to be the front man
for a really dull band.

327
00:17:59,573 --> 00:18:03,877
Finally, I bartered my eyesight
away to God,

328
00:18:03,877 --> 00:18:05,412
and that's the end.

329
00:18:05,412 --> 00:18:06,813
Why to God?

330
00:18:06,813 --> 00:18:09,283
Well, who the hell else
was I gonna give it to.

331
00:18:09,283 --> 00:18:12,486
Look, I don't expect you
to understand what I'm saying,

332
00:18:12,486 --> 00:18:16,623
but one day, if you find
yourself in a similar situation,

333
00:18:16,623 --> 00:18:19,193
make sure you handle it well.

334
00:18:19,193 --> 00:18:22,028
[Yu] It's just
at the top of this hill.

335
00:18:22,028 --> 00:18:24,798
I need you to walk
a little further, OK?

336
00:18:24,798 --> 00:18:26,400
[Sala] All right.

337
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:27,668
Sorry about this.

338
00:18:27,668 --> 00:18:30,537
I feel like a jerk,
dragging you all over the place.

339
00:18:30,537 --> 00:18:33,107
What? Give yourself
some credit, kid.

340
00:18:33,107 --> 00:18:36,277
You're a kind person.
That much I'm sure of.

341
00:18:36,277 --> 00:18:39,113
But you weren't always
like this, now, were you?

342
00:18:39,113 --> 00:18:42,549
Well, uh, never thought of it,
but you're probably right.

343
00:18:42,549 --> 00:18:46,287
Sometimes people change us
for the better.

344
00:18:48,855 --> 00:18:53,194
[Yu] <i>My mind instantly turned</i>
<i>to Tomori at that thought.</i>

345
00:18:53,194 --> 00:18:55,829
<i>So she influenced me?</i>

346
00:18:55,829 --> 00:18:59,200
[Tomori on phone]
<i>You're trying my patience here.</i>
<i>What is it?</i>

347
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:02,469
I want your big brother to meet
with Sala for a little bit.

348
00:19:02,469 --> 00:19:05,306
‐Why?
‐Because he's a fan.

349
00:19:05,306 --> 00:19:08,175
‐And he's been
into Zhiend's music forever.
<i>‐And?</i>

350
00:19:08,175 --> 00:19:10,311
And then something might happen
if they meet.

351
00:19:10,311 --> 00:19:13,547
Do I have to spell it out
for you?

352
00:19:13,547 --> 00:19:15,015
<i>What would happen?</i>

353
00:19:15,015 --> 00:19:17,584
[Yu] Come on.
He might become sane again.

354
00:19:17,584 --> 00:19:20,086
<i>That would never happen,</i>
<i>and you know it.</i>

355
00:19:20,086 --> 00:19:22,856
Maybe, but I'd still like
to believe it could.

356
00:19:22,856 --> 00:19:24,358
[Tomori sighs]

357
00:19:24,358 --> 00:19:27,294
[Tomori] I guess it's not
certain either way.

358
00:19:27,294 --> 00:19:29,095
Go ahead and give it a shot.

359
00:19:29,095 --> 00:19:30,664
[Yu] <i>Thank you.</i>

360
00:19:30,664 --> 00:19:33,767
[Tomori] But why do you care
about my brother so much?

361
00:19:33,767 --> 00:19:35,569
<i>Well, I, uh...</i>

362
00:19:35,569 --> 00:19:37,771
[Yu thinking]
<i>That's a good point.</i>

363
00:19:37,771 --> 00:19:41,375
<i>I've always been</i>
<i>the kind of person</i>
<i>who looks out for himself.</i>

364
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:43,777
[Tomori] <i>Is something wrong?</i>

365
00:19:43,777 --> 00:19:45,112
Nothing.

366
00:19:45,112 --> 00:19:46,947
Just a whim, I guess.

367
00:19:46,947 --> 00:19:49,583
[Tomori] <i>Huh. It's still weird,</i>
<i>but...</i>

368
00:19:49,583 --> 00:19:50,951
<i>thank you very much.</i>

369
00:19:50,951 --> 00:19:52,786
Then can you let
the hospital know

370
00:19:52,786 --> 00:19:55,689
that Sala and I should be there
sometime this evening?

371
00:19:55,689 --> 00:19:58,559
<i>Sure. No problem.</i>

372
00:20:00,327 --> 00:20:02,563
[Yu] I don't know what condition
he's in right now.

373
00:20:02,563 --> 00:20:04,598
You might want
to steel yourself for this.

374
00:20:04,598 --> 00:20:06,633
[Sala] Don't worry.
I can tell this is

375
00:20:06,633 --> 00:20:09,770
some heavy stuff just by
the sound of your voice.

376
00:20:09,770 --> 00:20:14,241
[screaming]

377
00:20:15,342 --> 00:20:17,578
Damn it, the painkillers
wore off again.

378
00:20:17,578 --> 00:20:20,481
I'm getting a very strange
vibe from this guy.

379
00:20:20,481 --> 00:20:24,084
So, do you have any idea
what he's doing right now?

380
00:20:24,084 --> 00:20:26,620
Uh, I think he's composing.

381
00:20:26,620 --> 00:20:30,124
Really? This is a lot heavier
than I expected.

382
00:20:30,124 --> 00:20:32,659
He was a big fan
of your band in the past.

383
00:20:32,659 --> 00:20:36,763
He was about to make
his debut as a guitarist
for a major label.

384
00:20:36,763 --> 00:20:39,032
[Sala] I see.

385
00:20:39,032 --> 00:20:41,135
[screams continue]

386
00:20:41,135 --> 00:20:43,470
[Yu] Uh, hey!

387
00:20:48,742 --> 00:20:52,078
<i>♪ Looking up high ♪</i>

388
00:20:52,078 --> 00:20:53,980
[screams continue]

389
00:20:53,980 --> 00:20:58,852
<i>♪ Found a steel tower ♪</i>

390
00:20:58,852 --> 00:21:03,490
<i>♪ Wondering how I would feel ♪</i>

391
00:21:03,490 --> 00:21:09,196
‐♪ If I fall down ♪
‐[screaming stops]

392
00:21:09,196 --> 00:21:13,967
<i>♪ Was it a dream ♪</i>

393
00:21:13,967 --> 00:21:19,306
<i>♪ I saw deep red ♪</i>

394
00:21:20,507 --> 00:21:26,113
<i>♪ Chasing all</i>
<i>that's far ahead ♪</i>

395
00:21:26,113 --> 00:21:29,750
<i>♪ Always yearning ♪</i>

396
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:31,385
<i>♪ Don't know why ♪</i>

397
00:21:31,385 --> 00:21:36,823
<i>♪ About the beauty</i>
<i>I really want ♪</i>

398
00:21:36,823 --> 00:21:40,394
<i>♪ May seem to be awkward ♪</i>

399
00:21:40,394 --> 00:21:45,031
<i>♪ To someone's eyes ♪</i>

400
00:21:48,469 --> 00:21:52,038
Kazuki Tomori. I'm a friend
of someone that you know.

401
00:21:52,038 --> 00:21:55,976
Do you remember
a girl named Nao,
your little sister?

402
00:21:59,012 --> 00:22:00,447
N...ao.

403
00:22:00,447 --> 00:22:03,884
That's right, your sister!

404
00:22:03,884 --> 00:22:05,119
Nao.

405
00:22:05,119 --> 00:22:07,721
Ah! Thank goodness.

406
00:22:07,721 --> 00:22:11,258
[Sala] Seems like some sort
of miracle just happened.

407
00:22:11,258 --> 00:22:14,728
Yeah. Your song
was able to reach him.

408
00:22:14,728 --> 00:22:17,598
You seem happy
from the bottom of your heart.

409
00:22:17,598 --> 00:22:20,934
And that makes me
just as happy.

410
00:22:20,934 --> 00:22:22,736
Yeah.

411
00:22:22,736 --> 00:22:24,638
Thanks.

412
00:22:26,607 --> 00:22:29,943
[Sala] Congratulations.
You moved one step forward.

413
00:22:29,943 --> 00:22:32,012
Hey, I can't thank you enough.

414
00:22:32,012 --> 00:22:35,949
I'm glad I was able to spend
such a fruitful day
with a brand‐new friend.

415
00:22:35,949 --> 00:22:40,020
By the way, I managed
to snag a couple of tickets
to see your gig tomorrow night.

416
00:22:40,020 --> 00:22:43,056
Yeah? Then even though I won't
be able to see you out there,

417
00:22:43,056 --> 00:22:45,159
I'll be sure to
sing my heart out for you.

418
00:22:45,159 --> 00:22:49,163
I'm guessing that the other
ticket's for that friend
you care about?

419
00:22:49,163 --> 00:22:51,698
I'll sing for her, too, then.

420
00:22:51,698 --> 00:22:53,700
Yeah, please do.

421
00:22:54,768 --> 00:22:56,670
[Yu] So in the end,

422
00:22:56,670 --> 00:22:58,239
Tomori, you were the one

423
00:22:58,239 --> 00:23:00,541
that changed me.

424
00:23:00,541 --> 00:23:03,377
[woman singing in Japanese]

425
00:23:07,114 --> 00:23:09,816
[phone rings]

426
00:23:09,816 --> 00:23:12,018
Hey, Otosaka speaking.

427
00:23:12,018 --> 00:23:13,520
[Tomori] <i>It's Tomori.</i>

428
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:16,056
Do you want to hear what
happened with your big brother?

429
00:23:16,056 --> 00:23:17,524
<i>I already know.</i>

430
00:23:17,524 --> 00:23:20,527
<i>I'm standing outside</i>
<i>the hospital right now.</i>

431
00:23:20,527 --> 00:23:22,529
We must have
just missed each other.

432
00:23:22,529 --> 00:23:25,532
<i>Yeah. I rushed over</i>
<i>after the nurses called</i>

433
00:23:25,532 --> 00:23:27,134
<i>to tell me what happened.</i>

434
00:23:27,134 --> 00:23:30,003
<i>Kazuki actually recognized me.</i>

435
00:23:30,003 --> 00:23:33,740
<i>It's been a long time since</i>
<i>I've seen my brother like that.</i>

436
00:23:33,740 --> 00:23:35,376
I'm really glad.

437
00:23:35,376 --> 00:23:38,279
<i>Yes. You made</i>
<i>a wonderful decision.</i>

438
00:23:38,279 --> 00:23:41,115
<i>I want you to know</i>
<i>I'm grateful.</i>

439
00:23:42,883 --> 00:23:44,551
[Tomori] Thank you very much.

440
00:23:44,551 --> 00:23:45,919
[Yu] Yeah.

441
00:23:45,919 --> 00:23:47,988
[Tomori] <i>So, I'll see you</i>
<i>again tomorrow.</i>

442
00:23:47,988 --> 00:23:51,125
<i>You haven't forgotten</i>
<i>about the gig, have you?</i>

443
00:23:51,125 --> 00:23:52,559
[Yu] Course not.

444
00:23:55,362 --> 00:23:58,465
[soft music plays]

445
00:23:58,465 --> 00:24:02,136
[Yu] <i>So tomorrow</i>
<i>I'll hear her songs live.</i>

446
00:24:02,136 --> 00:24:05,539
<i>Why does it feel</i>
<i>so nostalgic?</i>

